name: Achatina
description: The Achatina is a massive snail, mostly used for its production of Cementing Paste, or as a pet. This creature produces its paste passively ‚Äî and quite frequently ‚Äî so many survivors keep them around their bases. However, its usefulness pretty much ends there, as it cannot attack and moves quite slow. The Achatina must be tamed violently.
tamingNotice: üç∞ WARNING: The Achatina has a taming bug where it will momentarily act as though there is no food in its inventory after it eats each Cake, causing taming progress to drop slightly every time. Dododex's taming values have been adjusted to attempt to factor in this bug, however, the bug's impact is difficult to simulate perfectly. Dododex's values should not be off by more than one or two, but please bring a few extra cakes just in case. To help me improve these calculations, please use the 'Report Data Error' button if your in-game numbers are more than one off.

name: Allosaurus
description: The Allosaurus is a pack-hunting theropod that's smaller but faster than Rex. When in packs of 3 or more, the highest level Allosaurus will become the pack leader, emitting a red aura and making it stronger in battle.

name: Amargasaurus
description: The Amargasaurus is an upcoming tamable spiny sauropod in the Lost Island free DLC.
tamingNotice: To tame an Amargasaurus, you must first sync your tempermant with it. After syncing, you must hunt with it by attacking other creatures with it nearby. It will ocassionally ask for Exceptional Kibble. The Amargasaurus' taming meter increases with the amount of damage you inflict on nearby creatures. Dododex shows the total number of damage you must inflict under "Damage While Hunting."
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Andrewsarchus
description:
The Andrewsarchus is a warthog-like creature in ARK: Survival Evolved that is included in the free DLC map, Fjordur, which was released on June 12, 2022. The Andrewsarchus has the ability to charge ‚Äî both on land and in deep water. While charging, it has very limited turning capabilities. The Andrewsarchus eats honey and sweet fruit. Once tamed, its saddle can be mounted with a mini-gun. Since it is also acquatic, it can gather pearls.

Fjordur is a nordic-themed map originally created as a mod by Nekatus and Trappel, but will released as an official map on June 12, 2022. The map features lush forests, deepsea areas to explore, and beautiful landscapes. Fjordur includes four islands: Vardiland, Vannaland, Bolbjord, and Balheimr.
tamingNotice:
To tame an Andrewsarchus:

1. Wear a Ghille suit.
2. Put Giant Bee Honey on your hotbar and use it to throw the honey onto the ground.
3. While it eats, approach and and mount it.
4. Steer left and right as indicated by the arrows.
5. You will then be thrown off of the Andrewsarchus. Repeat.

Note that the number of required honey varies depending on how perfect you steer the Andrewsarchus. Dododex's calculations are based on a number of real in-game tests. To help improve these calculations, use the 'Report Data Error' button and provide the % taming increase after ONE ride.

name: Ammonite
description: While the Ammonite cannot be tamed, it is often hunted as its bile can be used to make powerful antidotes.

name: Ankylosaurus
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Archaeopteryx
description: The Archaeopteryx is a tree-dwelling bird-like dinosaur. While its smaller frame make it unfit for riding, it is strong enough to carry humans, allowing them to glide across long distances. Taming an Archaeopteryx is no simple task, as it will immediately flee when approached, and once knocked out, it prefers to eat rare insect matter.

name: Astrocetus
description: The Astrocetus is a giant space whale that has the ability to warp through hyperspace.
tamingNotice: To tame an Astrocetus, you must first knock it out by hitting its head. Using a Cannon mounted on a Tek Skiff is a common KO technique. Use the Tips feature to share your Astrocetus taming strategy!

name: Astrodelphis
description: The Astrodelphis is a space dolphin creature in ARK: Genesis Part 2. The Astrodelphis will be similar to the Astrocetus, but smaller. With excellent maneuverability and ability to roll and dodge, the Astrodelphis makes a great anti-air fighter. More details about the Astrodelphis will become available over time.
tamingNotice: To tame an Astrodelphis - you must pet it several times and then feed it Element and then repeat. Each time you feed, the Astrodelphis will require a set number of Element. The first feeding will be 1, then 3, 5, and 10, and then cycle back to 1. Have a good strategy? Share a tip!

name: Baryonyx
description: The Baryonyx is a large crocodile-like predator. While it might lack in attack power, its ability to swim extremtly fast makes it a fierce opponent ‚Äî especially with its ability to travel on both land and in water.

name: Basilisk
description: The Basilisk is a fearsome snake-like creature in ARK: Aberration.

name: Basilosaurus
description: The Basilosaurus is a dolphin-like creature that primarily dwells along the shallow areas of the ocean. It has the ability to keep survivors warm or cool.

name: Beelzebufo
description: One of the island's most useful amphibians, the beelzebufo can create cementing paste in its stomach simply by eating insects. Incredibly fast when hopping, its jumps can traverse vast expanses at the cost of little to no stamina. The beelzebufo can swim especially well and is one of the few creatures that can cause torpor using its attack. While it may be a little difficult to tame safely, many survivors consider it an especially useful addition to their tribes.

name: Beyla
description: Beyla is a boss in ARK: Fjordur.

name: Beyla Spawn
description: The Beyla Spawn is the minion of Beyla in ARK: Fjordur.

name: Bloodstalker
description: The Bloodstalker is spider-like creature in ARK: Genesis found in the bogs.
tamingNotice: Put Blood Packs in your inventory and let the Bloodstalker trap you and consume the Blood Packs. Let it eat a few tamed creatures to increase effectiveness. ‚ÑπÔ∏è After selecting your level, use the calculations in the row that matches your Bloodstalker's level. For example, for a Level 120 Bloodstalker, use the row labeled ("Lvl 1-140") ‚ö†Ô∏è IMPORTANT: The required amount of Blood Packs will vary by up to 25% with each Bloodstalker. Based on numerous tests and user reports, Dododex shows the estimated average required. Your total may be a bit higher or lower. Always bring at least 25% more.

name: Brontosaurus
description: The Brontosaurus is a behemoth of a dinosaur with a powerful tail 'tail sweep' attack that can smash all nearby enemies. This method is also one of the most efficient ways to gather berries and thatch, and the Brontosaurus' ability to carry large quantities of items make it even more useful for gathering. With its ability to carry a Platform Saddle, the Brontosaurus is often considered a must-have dinosaur for nomadic tribes looking for a mobile base.
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Broodmother Lysrix
tamingNotice: The Broodmother Lysrix is one of the bosses. Have a good strategy on how to battle Broodmother Lysrix? Share a tip!

name: Bulbdog
description: The Bulbdog (originally referred to as a 'Lantern Pug') is a cute bulldog-like creature in Ark: Aberration with a glowing orb antenna. The Bulbdog can be carried on a human's shoulder. It is a passive tame.

name: Carbonemys
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Carcharodontosaurus
description: Carcharodontosaurus is a therapod in ARK: Survival Evolved. It was released on November 5, 2022.
tamingNotice:
To tame a Carcharodontosaurus, you first need to trap it. Carry dinosaur corpses to the trapped Carcharodontosaurus and it will eat. A "trust" progress meter will appear above it.

Once the meter is filled, ride it and a taming bar will appear. Kill creatures while riding the Carcharodontosaurus to fill up its taming bar.

Check Dododex's Tips feature for taming strategies!

name: Castoroides
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Chalicotherium
description: The Chalicotherium is a mammal commonly found in colder areas that many survivors find useful in battle. In the wild, Chalicotherium often playfully throw snowballs and mud rocks at each other, however, when tamed, they can be given boulders to throw at enemy structures.

name: Cnidaria
description: The Cnidaria is a small jellyfish found in the oceans. This easy-to-spot creature won't attack unless approached too closely. It delivers a sedative sting that can knock out enemies if striked repeatedly. While it cannot be tamed, survivors will hunt it to gather its sedative, which is used for advanced tranquilizers.

name: Coelacanth
tamingNotice: The Coelacanth can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.

name: Corrupted Master Controller
description: The Corrupted Master Controller is a boss in ARK: Genesis (Part 1).

name: Daeodon
description: The Daeodon (or 'Hell Pig') is a vicious pig. This pig has a high healing and food consumption rate, making it difficult to maintain. It can be tamed and ridden, however, taming it is quite a difficult task.

name: Deathworm
tamingNotice: The Deathworm is not tamable. It can be found in the outer deserts of Scorched Earth. Have a good strategy on how to battle it? Share a tip!

name: Defense Unit
tamingNotice: This creature's Dododex profile may contain spoilers. Have a good strategy on how to battle the Defense Unit? Share a tip!

name: Deinonychus
description: The Deinonychus is an agile dino with sharp claws that can pounce and feed on its victim. The Deinonychus can also climb up walls by jumping. This creature is able to climb by jumping from wall to wall. It is very territorial around its nest.
tamingNotice: The Deinonychus can only be tamed by raising it from an egg. It can only be found in the Valguero map. Have a good strategy on obtaining Deinonychus eggs and raising them? Share it as a taming tip!

name: Desert Titan
description: The Desert Titan is a massive, flying, tamable mini-boss in ARK: Extinction.
tamingNotice: To tame a Desert Titan, you must destroy the corruption on its body. Taming effectiveness will drop if you hurt the Titan, so try to focus on the corruption. Titans come pre-equipped with a Platform Saddle, however, they are piloted from a seperate cockpit. Titans are a 24 hour temporary tame.

name: Desmodus
description: ü¶á The Desmodus Draculae is a bat in ARK: Survival Evolved that's included in the free DLC map, Fjordur, which was released on June 12, 2022.
tamingNotice:
The Desmodus is a passive tame. Put Blood Packs on your hot bar and let it grab you. It will consume 10 Blood Packs over a short period of time, then drop you. Repeat until tamed.

NOTE: ARK has not yet released 3D models of the Desmodus. Please continue to enjoy Dododex's artist rendition.

name: Dilophosaur
description: A Dilophosaur is a small, relatively weak dinosaur. Still, they're easy to tame for newer survivors, and are not hard to manage. They serve as guard dogs or pack-hunters, but are easily killed. Don't get too attached to them, as they likely won't survive combat against stronger dinosaurs.

name: Dinopithecus
description: The Dinopithecus is a tamable and ridiable giant baboon in the Lost Island free DLC. After ARK ran a community voting contest, this creature was the top voted of the ten semi-finalists with 6,214 votes (and 35% of the total vote).
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Diplocaulus
description: The Diplocaulus is a swamp amphibian with one major use once tamed; becoming a living oxygen bag. When swimming to the depths of the ocean, some disgusting survivors will suck on the bladders of a tamed diplocaulus' head as an effective oxygen source.

name: Diplodocus
description: The Diplodocus is a smaller sauropod best known for its ten-person (plus one driver) saddle, making it an excellent dino for group transport.

name: Dodo
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Doedicurus
description: Note: The Doedicurus can gather Obsidian from a small number of rocks, such as the ones on the volcano on The Island. It cannot gather Obsidian from most usual Obsidian rocks.
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Dung Beetle
tamingNotice: Massive Animal Feces cannot be used to tame the Dung Beetle.

name: Electrophorus
description: The Electrophorus is an electric eel with the ability to shock its targets.

name: Enforcer
description: The Enforcer is a craftable and rideable synthetic creature in ARK: Extinction that can climb walls, strafe, and make short teleportation jumps.
tamingNotice: Enforcer Blueprints can be obtained by killing Enforcers in the wild. The higher the level Enforcer you kill, the higher quality the Blueprint. Have a good technique on battling Enforcers? Share it as a tip!

name: Equus
description: The Equus is a horse-like creature that can be mounted with special saddles. While mounted, survivors can use whips and lassos.
tamingNotice: To tame the Equus, you must mount it immediately after the first feeding. Tap the action button each time you're prompted to feed again.

name: Eurypterid
description: The Eurypterid is not tamable. It can usually be found on the bottom of the ocean floor but sometimes travels to beaches as well.

name: Featherlight
description: The Featherlight is a tamable bird-like creature in Ark: Aberration.

name: Fenrir
description: The Fenrir is an wolf in ARK: Survival Evolved that is included in the free DLC map, Fjordur. It was released on June 12, 2022.
tamingNotice: The Fenrir cannot be found in the wild. To acquire one, you must defeat the final boss of Fjordur.

name: Fenris√∫lfr
description: Fenris√∫lfr is a boss in ARK: Fjordur.

name: Ferox
tamingNotice: To tame a Ferox, you must use Element near it and then survive after it evolves into its larger form. Use element near it again, and repeat.

name: Fjordhawk
description: The Fjordhawk is a scavenging bird in ARK: Survival Evolved that is included in the free DLC map, Fjordur, on June 12, 2022. It can fetch items and locate injured targets. After dying, the Fjordhawk can retrieve and return your items once you die.
tamingNotice:
To tame a Fjordhawk, you must let it eat creatures you kill (wild or tamed). The taming increase varies depending on the creature it eats.

Based on Dododex's testing of dozens of creatures, it generally prefers larger creatures such as the Brontosaurus, Diplodocus, or Parcer (all three were equal), however the size is not always correlated to how effective the creature is. The Ovis is the most effective creature to feed it. The Phiomia tames it very well in comparison to other easy-to-hunt dinos (even outperforming the Allosaurus and the Therizinosaurus).

Note that the level of the creature it eats does not matter (a level 1 will increase the taming bar just as much as a level 150).

Share which creatures worked best for you using the 'Tips' feature!

name: Forest Titan
description: The Forest Titan is a massive, tamable mini-boss in ARK: Extinction.
tamingNotice: To tame a Forest Titan, you must destroy the corruption on its body. Taming effectiveness will drop if you hurt the Titan, so try to focus on the corruption. Titans come pre-equipped with a Platform Saddle, however, they are piloted from a seperate cockpit. Titans are a 24 hour temporary tame.

name: Gacha
description: The Gacha is a tamable, ridable sloth-like creature with rocks on its back in ARK: Extinction. The Gacha has a unique "Crafting Skill" that allows the Gacha to transform a given resource into a desired item. The exact details on these resources are not yet available.
tamingNotice: Taming values are in stacks of ten. 3 "Metal Structures (10)" means 30. The Gacha also eats any type of weapons and armor, and the required quantity scales expectedly based on the resources needed (for example, 1 Shotgun is the equivalent of 5 Bows or 10 Slingshots). The required resources to tame a Gacha only slightly increase with higher levels (resources for a level 150 are only slightly higher than a level 1). Taming effectiveness is an estimation. Have any more details about the Gacha? Share it as a tip!

name: Gallimimus
description: The Gallimimus is extremely fragile, but its power to outrun everything gained place in the hearts of survivors who look for a mount to explore and scout the island by land, or just want to evade battle. This creature is unable to harvest most resources or attack enemy, but its reputation as fastest creature sure make it a valuable mount.
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Gasbags
description: The Gasbags is a massive, chubby tamable creature in ARK: Extinction. This Gas Boi has a multi-passenger saddle, allowing another survivor to ride on its behind. The Gasbags can inhale and then either float around or propel enemies away.
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Giant Bee
description: The Giant Bee builds its nest at the tops of Redwood trees. While it's not an easy task, a nest can be broken open and the queen can be tamed. Once tamed, she will generate honey as well as lay drone eggs.
tamingNotice: To tame a Queen Giant Bee, you must first destroy her nest. The nest has 5,000 health.

name: Giganotosaurus
tamingNotice: üèπ Tip: The Giga's torpor rate is significantly higher than any other creature. This means that if you miss a shot or wait too long between shots, the Giga's torpor will quickly start depleting, canceling out a shot per second or even more, resulting in more total shots required. Like all dinos, aim your shots for every 5 seconds (not slower or faster). Dododex's Giga KO calculations have been extensively tested and verified for accuracy.

name: Glowbug
description: The Glowbug is a firefly-like creature in Ark: Aberration. Creatures with charges can extract a charge from Glowbugs. They can be found in all biomes other than the surface.
tamingNotice: The Glowbug is a firefly-like creature in Ark: Aberration.

name: Glowtail
description: The Glowtail is a lizard-like creature in Ark: Aberration.

name: Griffin
tamingNotice: For the Griffin on ARK: Mobile, see the 'Royal Griffin.'

name: Hati & Sk√∂ll
description: Hati & Sk√∂ll are a boss in ARK: Fjordur.

name: Hesperornis
description: The Hesperornis is a flightless aquatic bird.
tamingNotice: To tame a Hesperornis, you must kill a fish, and drag the fish's corpse to the Hesperornis to feed it. The fish's size plays a major factor in how many fish will be required (a 1.0x fish appears to fill up the taming bar twice as much as a 0.5x fish). Level of fish does not appear to impact taming. The Sabertooth Salmon is by far the most effective fish, equivalent of about 4 Coels of the same size, while the Piranha is equivalent to about 2.4 Coels.

name: Hyaenodon
description: The Hyaenodon is a Hyaena-like creature.

name: Ice Titan
description: The Ice Titan is a massive, tamable mini-boss in ARK: Extinction.
tamingNotice: To tame a Ice Titan, you must destroy the corruption on its body. Taming effectiveness will drop if you hurt the Titan, so try to focus on the corruption. Titans come pre-equipped with a Platform Saddle, however, they are piloted from a seperate cockpit. Titans are a 24 hour temporary tame.

name: Ichthyornis
description: The Ichthyornis is a seagull that can be tamed to fetch fish.

name: Iguanodon
description: The Iguanodon is a dinosaur with the unique ability to walk on either two or four legs. When walking on two, it can attack enemies with its front feet, and while walking on four, it can sprint without running out of stamina. The Iguanodon also has the ability to convert fruit and vegetables into seeds.
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Jerboa
description: While the Jerboa has little practical use, some survivors enjoy its companionship as a cuddly, shoulder-mounted pet. This mini kangaroo-like creature is able to sense upcoming weather changes and its behavior will indicate when a tribe might need to prepare. The Jerboa is easy to tame, however, low torpor means survivors need to pay close attention to it while taming.
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Kaprosuchus
description: The Kaprosuchus is a crocodile-like reptile commonly found around swamps. Though it is a smaller, weaker version of the Sarco, some survivors perfer it for its speed ‚Äî both on land and in water.

name: Karkinos
description: The Karkinos is a massive crab-like creature in Ark: Aberration that can grab and smash creatures and players. It can also throw them at great lengths. Using its strong legs, the Karkinos can leap to impressive heights.
tamingNotice: To knock out a Karkinos, aim for its abdomen. Hitting its limbs will only inflict damage and not torpor.

name: Kentrosaurus
description: While the Kentrosaurus may appear to just be a version of the Stegosaurus, its strength should not be mistaken. With its sharp defensive spikes and deadly tail, the Kentrosaurus can even take on larger carnivores ‚Äî especially when in herds. Because of its sharp spines, saddling a Kentrosaurus is not possible.
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: King Titan
tamingNotice: The King Titan is a boss in ARK: Extinction. Have a good strategy on how to battle the King Titan? Share a tip!

name: Leech
tamingNotice: The Leech can only be tamed using a Fish Basket.

name: Leedsichthys
tamingNotice: The Leedsichthys cannot be tamed, however, it can be trapped so that tribes can scrape off Raw Prime Meat from its body without killing it.

name: Liopleurodon
description: The Liopleurodon is a aquatic reptile often found hiding in the reefs of the ocean.

name: Lymantria
description: The Lymantria is a moth-like creature that can expel a cloud of poisonous spores. While its slow flying speed make it a less suitable flying mount for transportation, survivors can use its spores to slow down enemies.
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Lystrosaurus
description: The Lystrosaurus is a small, common herbivore often used as a pet. While the Lystrosaurus will not fight, it can be useful to have around ‚Äî or as a companion on short hunting trips ‚Äî as it increases experience of nearby creatures and survivors. The Lystrosaurus must be tamed passively, making it very easy to acquire by any survivor with a handful of Rare Flowers.

name: Maewing
description: The Maewing is an "interstellar wet nurse" in ARK: Genesis Part 2. It resembles a platypus mixed with a flying squirrel and has some sort of ability to glide. The Maewing is described as an "interstellar wet nurse" and is able to lure offspring of other creatures using its irresistible teats. Nice! üòè
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Magmasaur
description: The Magmasaur is a large creature that can swim in lava. Its saddle is fire resistant.
tamingNotice: To tame a Magmasaur, you must steal a Magmasaur egg. Share your strategy in the Tips section!

name: Mammoth
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Managarmr
description: The Managarmr is a creature in ARK: Extinction.

name: Manticore
tamingNotice: The Manticore is a boss in Scorched Earth. Have a good strategy on how to battle Manticore? Share a tip!

name: Megachelon
tamingNotice: The Megachelon is a passive tame. To tame it, find a small swarm of fish, and lure them over to.a Megachelon. Swim along side the turtle with the swarm to tame it. Share your strategies in the Tips section!

name: Megaloceros
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Megalosaurus
description: The megalosaurus is one of the strongest therapods, but its nocturnal sleeping pattern make it significantly less effective during the day. The megalosaurus can bite and even latch onto enemies ‚Äî including humans ‚Äî and swing them around, hindering their ability to move. This carnivore is stronger than a Carno or a Rex at night, but during the day, it is much more slow and sluggish.

name: Mega Mek
description: The Mek is a mechanical creature in ARK: Extinction.
tamingNotice: To create a Mega Mek, you must combine four Meks using a M.O.M.I., which is obtained after defeating the King Titan.

name: Megapithecus
tamingNotice: The Megapithecus is one of the bosses in Ark. Have a good strategy on how to battle Megapithecus? Share a tip!

name: Mek
description: The Mek is a mechanical creature in ARK: Extinction.

name: Microraptor
description: The Microraptor is a tiny, agile dinosaur with the ability to attack predators while ignoring their mounts. Its wings also give it the ability to glide after leaping.

name: Moeder
description: The Moeder is a underwater mini-boss.

name: Morellatops
description: The Morellatops is a camel-like creature that has the ability to store water in its hump. It can be essential as a pack animal when transporting supplies through the hot, dry desert. The Morellatops will flee once attacked, but once knocked out, it is a relatively easy creature to tame.
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Mosasaurus
description: An elusive marine lizard and reputed as one of the largest creature found in the waters, the Mosasaurus is much more powerful than any known aquatic beast encountered in the depth. While its sluggish speed may put off some survivors, being ambushed by one can mean a certain death.

name: Moschops
description: The Moschops is a omnivorous therapsid best known for its love for food. Survivors can train it to favour specific types of food ‚Äî whether it be Prime Meat or Rare Flowers ‚Äî and it will become more effective at gathering it. The Moschops is a very cowardly creature and will flee from any sight of danger.
tamingNotice: The Moschops eats Sap, Giant Bee Honey, Leech Blood, Rare Mushrooms, Rare Flowers, Organic Polymer, Raw & Cooked Meat, Raw & Cooked Prime Meat, Raw & Cooked Prime Fish Meat, and Berries. Each time you feed it, its desired food will change. Have a good Moschops taming technique? Share a tip!

name: Nameless
description: The Nameless is an untamable chupacabra-like creature in Ark: Aberration. The alpha Nameless will slowly spawn other Nameless over time.
tamingNotice: The Nameless is an untamable creature in ARK: Aberration.

name: Noglin
description: The Noglin is a mind-bending creature in ARK: Genesis Part 2. The Noglin allows you to temporarily take control over creatures (wild or tamed) and even humans.
tamingNotice: To tame a Noglin, you must let it latch onto your own tames.

name: Otter
tamingNotice: To tame an otter, kill some fish, approach the otter, and then use the action button to feed the fish to it. Level of fish does not impact taming. The Sabertooth Salmon is by far the most effective fish, followed by the Piranha and the Coelacanth. Please ignore timing and effectiveness as calculations are not yet complete.

name: Overseer
tamingNotice: The Overseer is the final boss in Ark: Survival Evolved. This creature's Dododex profile may contain spoilers. Have a good strategy on how to battle The Overseer? Share a tip!

name: Ovis
description: The ovis is a sheep-like creature that many survivors find useful in farming. It can be found in the grasslands. While rare, it can be tamed simply by feeding it one Sweet Vegetable Cake. This sheep can be sheered with Scissors to obtain Wool, or killed to obtain Mutton. While the ovis can be mounted, it is not an ideal mount for transport and provides very little use once mounted, other than its ability to climb up steep inclines.

name: Pachy
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Pachyrhinosaurus
description: The Pachyrhinosaurus is a herbivore with a unique ability to manipulate its enemies. This cunning dinosaur can emit two types of mists that manipulates most nearby creatures to be either passive or aggressive. This allows survivors to safely travel through a dangerous area or even herd a group of vicious creatures to use against an enemy. The Pachyrhinosaurus is slightly larger than the Triceratops, and wears a two-person saddle once tamed.
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Paraceratherium
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Parasaur
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Pegomastax
description: The Pegomastax is a small herbivore popular among farmers. The Pegomastax has an exceptional skill of gathering seeds and berries, while also able to gather rare ingredients such as Rare Flowers and Rare Mushrooms. While it is relatively weak, this small dinosaur will become quite agressive if provoked.

name: Pelagornis
description: The Pelagornis is a versatile pelican-like bird and the only creature able to walk, fly, and surface-swim.

name: Phiomia
description: While the Phiomia does not attack, many survivors see value in it as an easy-to-tame pack animal. It will quickly flee when attempting to knock it out, but once tranquilized, the Phiomia can be tamed very quickly, making it a popular choice for survivors looking for a creature to transport supplies. The Phiomia produces a lot of feces in comparison to other creatures, making it useful in fertilizer production.
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Phoenix
tamingNotice: To tame a Phoenix, shoot it with a flame arrow, flamethrower or Fire Wyvern. Weapon quality impacts taming speed; a 200% damage bow will be twice as fast as a 100% bow. Please ignore taming effectiveness and taming times as the Phoenix has unique calculations. Have a good taming technique idea? Share a tip!

name: Piranha
tamingNotice: The Piranha can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.

name: Pteranodon
description: The pteranodon is a fast and versatile flying mount useful for traveling and scouting, though not always the ideal choice for battle. Knocking a pteranodon out doesn't take much, but can still be a challenge since it will immediately flee after being attacked. Once knocked out, taming is quite easy in comparison to other creatures, and with its low saddle requirements, this makes it an especially popular creature for newer survivors while still being versatile enough for more experienced survivors. What the pterandon lacks in stamina, weight, and health, it makes up with its speed.

name: Purlovia
description: The Purlovia is a mammal with the unique ability to burrow underground and hibrinate. Using the technique, the Purlovia will pounce once a predator appears nearby.

name: Quetzal
description: The Quetzal is a behemoth of a creature with base stats that top the charts (health, stamina, weight, and torpor). The Quetzal's platform saddle make it an excellent choice for a mobile air base or even a caravan for transporting and gathering metal and other supplies on harder to reach areas. While its melee strength isn't as high as some might expect, its health and ability to carry weapons make it suitable to use as a war bird. Its preference for Rex Kibble make it difficult to tame, and even more so difficult to knock out in the air.

name: Raptor
description: The Raptor is a well-rounded and easy-to-tame dinosaur. Its high speed and ability to defend itself make it very useful for travel, especially for newer survivors. While the raptor has a lower torpor tolerance, its speed can often make it difficult to target.

name: Ravager
description: The Ravager is a tamable creature in Ark: Aberration.

name: Reaper
description: The Reaper King and Queen are creatures in Ark: Aberration.
tamingNotice: To tame a Reaper, you must get a Reaper Queen to impregnate you. Visit the Tips section to see detailed strategies ‚Äî or add your own!

name: Rock Drake
description: The Rock Drake is a gliding creature that has the ability to cloak itself and its rider. Using a Rock Drake's excellent climbing skills, survivors can traverse across steep cliffs. The Rock Drake can only be found in a particular cavern and is relatively tough to tame.
tamingNotice: The Rock Drake must be tamed like the Wyvern. To acquire one, you must steal and raise its egg.

name: Rock Elemental
description: The Rock Elemental is a massive rock monster that is typically found disguised as a stone formation. When a survivor enters its territory, it will begin thrashing and throwing large boulders. Once tamed, it can be a highly effective siege weapon to bring into battle.
tamingNotice: To knock out a Rock Elemental, you must target its head.

name: Rockwell
tamingNotice: Rockwell is a boss in ARK: Aberration. Have a good strategy on how to battle Rockwell? Share a tip!

name: Roll Rat
description: The Roll Rat is a tamable, rideable mole-like creature in Ark: Aberration. Almost like a more powerful Doedicurus, you can rapidly roll while mounted, plowing through enemies in its path with its spiked saddle. This advanced metal saddle can seat 6 survivors and must be repaired after repeatedly rolling.
tamingNotice: To tame a Roll Rat, wait until it burrows and underground then drop a food item into its burrow.

name: Royal Griffin
tamingNotice:
‚ö†Ô∏è ARK Mobile players: I am working on improving the accuracy of the Royal Griffin Kibble numbers. I made some improvements but please use the 'Report Data Error' button to let me know if your results are different than Dododex's ‚Äî even if it's off by one. Including the taming % increase per Kibble is super helpful. Please do not report errors through the Tips feature as I may miss it. ARK Mobile does not release their source files so I must rely on user testing. Thank you! ‚Äî@danlev 

The Royal Griffin is exclusive to ARK: Mobile. Remember: Your Dododex taming multiplier should be set to 0.875x for ARK Mobile. You can use Settings presets for ARK Mobile and Soothing Balms.

name: Rubble Bear
description: The Rubble Bear is the minion of Steinbj√∂rn in ARK: Fjordur.

name: Sabertooth Salmon
tamingNotice: The Sabertooth Salmon can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.

name: Scout
description: The Scout is a fast-flying, craftable Tek surveillance drone in ARK: Extinction. It can be remotely controlled, allowing survivors to scout areas. The Scout is powered by Element.

name: Seeker
description: The Seeker is a creature in Ark: Aberration.

name: Shadowmane
description: The Shadowmane is a chimerical prowler creature in ARK: Genesis Part 2.  It has a fast chain-teleport-strike attack that can hit multiple targets in a row. The Shadowmane can also cloak those around it. It has been described as the King of the Twisted, the Queen of the Coral Ridge, and the Arbiter of Shadows.
tamingNotice: To tame a Shadowmane, you must sneak up on it (crouch while wearing a Ghillie Suit or having consumed Cactus Broth) while it is sleeping. Feed it a Filled Fish Basket of at least 0.5x size. The type of fish does not matter and the level of the fish does not matter. Note that fish sizes in ARK are rounded. A 1.5 fish could actually be 1.45 or 1.54, which can make a noticable difference, so bring extra fish. NOTE: Timing has not been tested -- please ignore for now.

name: Shinehorn
description: The Shinehorn is a jackalope-like creature in Ark: Aberration.
tamingNotice: The Shinehorn is a creature in Ark: Aberration.

name: Sinomacrops
description: The Sinomacrops is a tamable pterosaur in the Lost Island free DLC.

name: Snow Owl
description: The Snow Owl is a flying creature in ARK: Extinction.

name: Stegosaurus
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Steinbj√∂rn
description: Steinbj√∂rn is a boss in ARK: Fjordur.

name: Tek Stryder
description: The Stryder is a robotic creature in ARK: Genesis Part 2. It offers a series of different randomized components across its body, giving each Stryder unique skills ‚Äî from offense to defense to utility.
tamingNotice: The Stryder can be tamed by "hacking" it using Mutagel. You must also complete a number of required missions. No more than 51 missions will be required for a single Stryder. The required Mutagel and missions both increase with the Stryder's level. Rigs are fixed to each stryder and cannot be crafted or interchanged. Share your tips and strategies about each Stryder rig using the "Utility" tips category!

name: Tapejara
description: The Tapejara is a versatile and highly maneuverable pterosaur known for its three-person saddle. While it may not have as much stamina and weight carrying capacity as other creatures, it has unique benefits in combat. The Tapejara can land on trees and other vertical surfaces, allowing both the pilot and the passengers to use weapons. Its rudder-like fin make it one of the few flying creatures able to hover and strafe side-to-side.

name: Therizinosaurus
description: The Tickle Chicken, also known by its more boring, scientific name, the Therizinosaurus, is a medium-sized, aggressive dinosaur. While it is slow and cannot carry much weight, it is a quite versatile mount, being very strong in battle and having the ability to gather resources effectively. The Therizinosaurus can be trained to gather specific types of resources for its rider.
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Thylacoleo
description: The Thylacoleo is a large, powerful mount that can climb up trees and pounce on its enemies.

name: Titanoboa
tamingNotice: The Titanoboa must be tamed with fertilized eggs. Drop an egg near it and it will consume it. The Titanoboa is not tamable in ARK Mobile. Timing and intervals are rough estimates, as the Titanoboa's eating pattern is unclear. Use the 'Report Data Error' button if any of your eggs differ.

name: Titanosaur
description: The Titanosaur is the largest creature in Ark whose stats top the charts across the board. This sauropod's massive platform saddle allows tribes to build large fortresses on its back ‚Äî if they're skilled enough to tame it.
tamingNotice: To knock out a Titanosaur, you must target its head.

name: Triceratops
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Trilobite
tamingNotice: The Trilobite can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.

name: Tropeognathus
description: The Tropeognathus is a ridable flying pterosaur. While they are not the fastest flyers, they have excellent stamina and are great for transportation. Its beak allows surviors to "recycle" items and gear to their base components.

name: Tusoteuthis
description: The Tusoteuthis is a massive, aggressive squid found in the depths of the oceans. In battle, the Tusoteuthis can grab its prey and knock it unconcious, siphoning its blood to gain health. Once tamed, the ink from a Tusoteuthis can be used as a constant Oil source. Some survivors choose to hunt the Tusoteuthis for its Oil.
tamingNotice: The Tusoteuthis's taming method differs from most creatures. Please ignore its interval and time calculations.

name: Unicorn
tamingNotice: To tame the Unicorn, you must mount it immediately after the first feeding. Tap the action button each time you're prompted to feed again. On ARK: Mobile, you can only use Griffin Kibble. Reminder for Mobile players: Your Dododex taming multiplier should be set to 0.875x for ARK Mobile. You can use Settings presets for ARK Mobile and Soothing Balms.

name: Velonasaur
description: The Velonasaur is a living turret in ARK: Extinction with a unique turrent-like spike-shooting attack. It can be enabled while you are not riding it. It also has the ability to swing its body back and forth to attack preys.

name: Voidwyrm
description: The Voidwyrm is a Tek Wyvern creature in ARK: Genesis Part 2.
tamingNotice: To tame a Voidwyrm you must first decrease its health to 10% and then mount it. Put Mutagen in your last hotbar slot and do a barrel roll to feed it Mutagen.

name: Woolly Rhino
food: Fresh Barley, Fresh Wheat, or Soybean

name: Wyvern
description: The Wyvern is a highly sought-after massive flying dragon that can overpower most creatures it faces. The deadly Wyvern, which is only tamable by stealing and raising as a baby, can be found in four varieities ‚Äî Fire, Ice, Lightning, and Poison ‚Äî each of which have distinct attacks.
tamingNotice: To tame a Wyvern, survivors must steal a Wyvern egg. Once hatched, Wyvern babies need to be fed Wyvern Milk, which can be obtained by knocking out a female Wyvern.

name: Yeti
description: The Yeti is an Alpha creature found in the Snow Cave. It cannot be tamed.
